{
  "description": "This quiz assesses knowledge of HTML5 semantic elements beyond basic tags like <div> and <span>, gauging the learner's ability to apply proper markup for improved accessibility and SEO. It is moderately challenging, using a light‑hearted, encouraging tone that nudges participants to adopt best practices. The quiz aims to reinforce semantic HTML skills while keeping the experience fun and motivational.",
  "topics": [
    "HTML5 semantic elements",
    "Proper use of <header>, <nav>, <section>, <article>, <footer>, etc.",
    "Accessibility and SEO considerations",
    "Difference between generic and semantic tags"
